In the Lagrangian, the position coordinates and velocity components are all independent variables, and derivatives of the Lagrangian are taken with respect to these separately according to the usual differentiation rules (e.g. the derivative of "L" with respect to the "z"-velocity component of particle 2, "v" = d"z"/d"t", is just that; no awkward chain rules or total derivatives need to be used to relate the velocity component to the corresponding coordinate "z").

